<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1163482>
    dc:description "Figs 180–188. Raveniola micropa species group, holotypic (180–181, 183–186) and conspecific (182, 187–188) ♂♂. Details of palpal organ; retrolateral (180, 182, 185, 187), ventral (181, 186, 188), retroventral (183) and prolateral (184) views. — 180–181. R. birecikensis sp. nov. 182. Same species as preceding (dwarf specimen?). 183. R. anadolu sp. nov. 184. R. arthuri Kunt & Yağmur, 2010. 185– 186. R. turcica sp. nov. 187–188. R. micropa (Ausserer, 1871). Scalebars: 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1163482/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1163488>
    dc:description "Figs 204–212. Raveniola spp., ♀♀. Vulva, dorsal views. — 204. R. nana sp. nov. (holotype). 205. R. turcica sp. nov. (paratype). 206. R. micropa (Ausserer, 1871) (Uludağ). 207. Same aspecies as preceding (holotype). 208. R. zaitzevi (Charitonov, 1948) (Lagodekhi). 209. Same species as preceding (Pirkuli). 210. R. vonwicki Zonstein, 2000 (paratype). 211. R. niedermeyeri (Brignoli, 1972) (paratype, Gorgan). 212. Same species as preceding (Mazandaran). Scale bars: 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1163488/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

